                            <comment id="14620279" author="sagara" created="Thu, 9 Jul 2015 10:25:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please find the following patch here &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; - &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cxf/pull/81&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cxf/pull/81&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14620305" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Thu, 9 Jul 2015 10:44:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you please tell which client does put 2 spaces in &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&quot;Basic  credentials&quot; 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For example, I&apos;m not sure the following is valid:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&quot;Basic                                              credentials&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;where it is 40 spaces, so why 2 spaces should be supported ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14620745" author="dkulp" created="Thu, 9 Jul 2015 16:03:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at the spec at &lt;a href=&quot;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7235#section-2.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7235#section-2.1&lt;/a&gt; , the &quot;credentials&quot; type is defined as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;credentials = auth-scheme [ 1*SP ( token68 / #auth-param ) ]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which means it needs at least one, but up to infinite, spaces.   Thus, this is valid.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14620787" author="sagara" created="Thu, 9 Jul 2015 16:27:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Sergey These are my concerns. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1.) I&apos;m not saying 2 spaces as a special case it&apos;s just an example it could be N number of spaces. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2.)  If a client send some invalid header content then server should not return NPE or ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException, instead  IMHO if security enabled server should returns 401 otherwise server should proceed into further processing.    &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The main problem here is above logic always expect 2 parts after splitting &apos;credentials&apos;, but when you have N number of spaces StringUtils.split() returns  3 parts also when you have only &quot;Basic&quot; as header content StringUtils.split() returns only 1 part.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
